@kb text
Use kb for explicit knowledge retrieval against the repository-backed KU catalog when the step is primarily about finding reusable guidance or content.
Prefer it when the runtime needs to discover which prompt asset, caller profile, policy note, or reusable content should shape the next step.
Good kb requests describe the topic, scope, and intended downstream use so the retrieved KUs can inform planning or execution transparently.
Do not use it as a substitute for planning or for generating new prose when the task is not actually about retrieving knowledge.
